MolFrame Tools¶

Created on Thu Aug 31, 2017 by A. Pahl

Tools for working with MolFrame dataframes.

class mol_frame.mol_frame.MolFrame(init=None, log=True)[source]¶

A wrapper class around Pandas DataFrame with added structure handling capabilities.

__getattr__(name)[source]¶

Try to call undefined methods on the underlying pandas DataFrame.

__weakref__¶

list of weak references to the object (if defined)

add_fp(fp_name='ecfc4')[source]¶

Adds a fingerprint column to the MolFrame. The available fingerprints can be viewed by: >>> print(mf.FDICT.keys())

Always operates in-place!

add_images(force=False)[source]¶

Adds ań Image column to the MolFrame, used for structure tooltips in plotting. Always operates in-place!

add_mols(force=False, remove_src=False)[source]¶

Adds mol objects to the MolFrame. Tries to use the Mol_b64 column. If that is not present, it uses Smiles. Always operates in-place!

add_smiles(isomeric_smiles=True)[source]¶

Adds Smiles column from mol objects to the MolFrame. Always operates in-place!

apply_to_col(col_name, new_col_name, lambda_func)[source]¶

Applies a func to a column in the MolFrame. A wrapper around pd.apply to enable progress bars. Returns a new copy or modifies inplace, depending on self.inplace.

apply_to_mol(new_col_name, lambda_func)[source]¶

Applies a func to the Mol object, which is generated on-the-fly, if necessary. Displays a progress bar for longer operations. Returns a new copy or modifies inplace, depending on self.inplace.

b64_from_smiles()[source]¶

Adds Mol_b64 column to MolFrame. Always operates in-place!

drop_cols(cols)[source]¶

Drops the list of columns from the DataFrame. Listed columns that are not present in the DataFrame are simply ignored (no error is thrown).

find_mol_col()[source]¶

Find a suitable mol column. Either Mol, Mol_b64 or Smiles.

groupby(by=None, num_agg=['median', 'mad', 'count'], str_agg='unique')[source]¶

Other str_aggs: “first”, “unique”.

id_filter(cpd_ids, reset_index=True, sort_by_input=False)[source]¶

Returns a new MolFrame instance consisting only of the give cpd_ids. When sort_by_input == True, the lines in the new MolFrame will have the same order as the given cpd_ids.

keep_cols(cols)[source]¶

Keeps the list of columns of the DataFrame. Listed columns that are not present in the DataFrame are simply ignored (no error is thrown).

load(fn, sep='\t')[source]¶

Read one or multiple result files and concatenate them into one MolFrame. fn is a single filename (string) or a list of filenames.

merge(other, on=None, how='left')[source]¶

Using pd.merge()

mol_filter(query, add_h=False)[source]¶

Substructure filter. Returns a new MolFrame instance. query has to be a Smiles string.

remove_mols()[source]¶

Remove the mol objects from the MolFrame. Always operates in-place!

remove_smiles_and_b64()[source]¶

Remove the Smiles and Mol_b64 columns from the MolFrame, if present. Always operates in-place!

scatter(x, y, colorby=None, options={}, styles={}, title='Scatter Plot', force=False)[source]¶

Possible options: width, height, legend_position [e.g. “top_right”] Possible styles: size, cmap [brg, Accent, rainbow, jet, flag, Wistia]

sim_filter(query, cutoff=0.75)[source]¶

Similarity filter. Returns a new MolFrame instance. Add a suitable fingerprint once with addf_fps(), then give a reference fingerprint as query.

view(title='MolFrame', include_smiles=False, drop=[], keep=[], fn='molframe.html', **kwargs)[source]¶

Known kwargs: selectable (bool), index (bool)
